name: Lily's Mexican Restaurant

name: University Puget Sound, Thompson

comment: The building is open until 6:00 pm for public access, and after 6:00 pm to students in the sciences. The fourth floor has a completely neutral bathroom, as well as a neutral shower.

name: University Puget Sound, Wheelock Student Center
directions: Second floor of the student center, towards the back of the building. (Take the main stairwell by the information desk and head backwards (near CHWS)).
comment: 24 Hour access. Generally a nice/accepting campus. (If not a student- look like you know what you're doing/going)

name: Next to Pershing Square Metro Station

name: Shay's

name: phoenix (lgbt) center

name: The Beer Trappe
directions: Bathrooms are located in the back.
comment: Both are single stall with doors that lock on the inside. One is \"family\" but either room is gender-neutral.

name: Downtown Arts Center
directions: Located in the back, ask employees where to go.

name: Lexington History Museum
directions: Wheelchair accessible entrance off of Cheapside. Women's bathroom not accessible.

name: Lexington Public Library - Central
directions: The main lobby is accessibly the via Phoenix Park or Main St. entrance.

There is one \"family/unisex\" bathroom on the 2nd Floor, all other bathrooms are gendered. Location is safe and locks work.

name: Chevy Chase Coin Laundry
directions: The back door is closest to the bathroom inside.
comment: Door locks from the inside and is secure. The location is safe.

name: Gratz Park Inn
directions: Used entrance on S. Upper St. side. There is a ramp to enter the building.

name: Carnegie Center For Literacy & Learning

comment: Monday-Thursday 9-7:30 pmFriday 9-5 pmSaturday 10-2 pmSunday CLOSED

name: Marathon Food Mart #49
directions: Bathroom is located on the outside of the building.
comment: There is only one so there is no gender specific option. The area is lighted somewhat but would be less secure at night. The door locks from the inside and is secure.

name: ucl anatomy
directions: ground floor. turn left at the end of the corridor.
comment: need a student card to enter.

name: Pembroke College
directions: Walk in through gate house on Trumpington street and turn right. Go through the 3rd door and there is a locking, single stall, non-gendered toilet on the ground floor.
comment: There is nothing to stop members of the public just going in there, tourists are always wandering round the college. If you get stopped by porters (I've never known this happen) explain you're going to the toilet, they may be concerned you are trying to burgle student accomodation.

name: Jade Palace
directions: On the left of the building in the back. It's in a weird nook.
comment: The bathrooms are unusually small.

name: Helios Cafe
directions: At the back of the building on the left.
comment: They do have a backdoor, so there is a possibility of sneaking in there.

name: Sushi Blues Cafe
directions: To the left of the bar at the back of the building.

name: Brueggers Bagels
directions: To the left of the register, middle of the building.

name: Global Village Coffee House
directions: On the left at the back of the building.

name: Jasmin Bistro
directions: To the right of the building down a hallway.

name: Port City Java
directions: Ask for key, it's to the right of the registers down a hallway.

directions: Use the door farthest to the left of the establishment. Walk past the bar to the end of the room, and on the right is a single stall.
comment: It does have a glass door, that may or may not make people uncomfortable. It's the fuzzy kind that old showers have.

name: Morning Times
directions: First floor to the right of the register, you need to ask for a key.

name: Jim's Wings

comment: 11 a.m. to 10 p.m. Monday through Saturday and 11 a.m. to 9 p.m. Sundays Best wings in Fort Collins

name: Biochemistry Building, Downing Site
directions: Through the doors, down the stairs and right in front of you on the left.

name: the fountain inn
directions: 2nd floor, unmarked most of the time

name: Portland Museum of Art
directions: Intersection of Congress, Free and High streets
comment: you might be able to get in free just to use the bathroom.

name: La Bagel Delight
directions: Walk straight back and it is the second door on your left in the seating area.
comment: Open early until 8 on weekdays, close earlier on weekends. The best bagel in the world so definitely order one!

name: Babeland
directions: back of the room, to the left
comment: not kid-friendly

name: Kitchenette
directions: back of the building by the kitchen
comment: great food, it's totally worth buying

name: UNLV

name: CMFA

name: Tinga Taqueria

name: Starbucks
street: Behind Starbucks,  High Chelmer Shopping Centre
directions: Go behind the bar of Starbucks towards what looks like a staff area. On your left is a toilet that looks like a disabled one. It's meant to be for costumers but you don't have to walk through starbucks to get to it so it's ok.
comment: Open as long as High Chelmer is. Not a bad toilet.

name: Stockholm C

name: Cafe de Paris

name: Tarkiln Bayou State Park

name: Woodlawn Beach Access

name: WRAC
directions: 2 single stall, locking restrooms: 1 on first floor (accessible), 1 on second floor (non-accessible)

name: Minor Hall
